    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn1.39:1.1",
          "pli": "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—",
          "en": "So I have heard. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.39:1.2",
          "pli": "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ. ",
          "en": "At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.39:1.3",
          "pli": "Atha kho kokanadā pajjunnassa dhītā abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ mahāvanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. ",
          "en": "Then, late at night, the beautiful Kokanadā, Pajjunna’s daughter, lighting up the entire Great Wood, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.39:1.4",
          "pli": "Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho sā devatā kokanadā pajjunnassa dhītā bhagavato santike imā gāthāyo abhāsi: ",
          "en": "and recited these verses in the Buddha’s presence: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.39:2.1",
          "pli": "“Vesāliyaṃ vane viharantaṃ, ",
          "en": "“Staying in the woods of Vesālī "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.39:2.2",
          "pli": "Aggaṃ sattassa sambuddhaṃ; ",
          "en": "is the Buddha, best of beings. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.39:2.3",
          "pli": "Kokanadāhamasmi abhivande, ",
          "en": "Kokanadā am I who worships him, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.39:2.4",
          "pli": "Kokanadā pajjunnassa dhītā. ",
          "en": "Kokanadā, Pajjuna’s daughter. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.39:3.1",
          "pli": "Sutameva pure āsi, ",
          "en": "Previously I had only heard "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.39:3.2",
          "pli": "Dhammo cakkhumatānubuddho; ",
          "en": "the teaching realized by the seer. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.39:3.3",
          "pli": "Sāhaṃ dāni sakkhi jānāmi, ",
          "en": "But now I know it as a witness "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.39:3.4",
          "pli": "Munino desayato sugatassa. ",
          "en": "while the sage, the Holy One teaches. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.39:4.1",
          "pli": "Ye keci ariyaṃ dhammaṃ, ",
          "en": "There are unintelligent people who go about "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.39:4.2",
          "pli": "Vigarahantā caranti dummedhā; ",
          "en": "denouncing the noble teaching. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.39:4.3",
          "pli": "Upenti roruvaṃ ghoraṃ, ",
          "en": "They fall into the terrible Hell of Screams "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.39:4.4",
          "pli": "Cirarattaṃ dukkhaṃ anubhavanti. ",
          "en": "where they suffer long. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.39:5.1",
          "pli": "Ye ca kho ariye dhamme, ",
          "en": "There are those who have found acceptance and peace "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.39:5.2",
          "pli": "Khantiyā upasamena upetā; ",
          "en": "in the noble teaching. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.39:5.3",
          "pli": "Pahāya mānusaṃ dehaṃ, ",
          "en": "After giving up this human body, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.39:5.4",
          "pli": "Devakāyaṃ paripūressantī”ti. ",
          "en": "they swell the hosts of gods.”"
        }
      ],
